We are looking for a switched-on individual who enjoys programming, is keen to
learn and who can converse at a strong technical level.

##  About Us

We have been selling online for over 14 years with continuing success and
growth. Part of this success is due to us developing our own tools for
managing our technical product data and order processing automation.

##  About the Role

The role requires the successful applicant to work in a small team and often
autonomously.

Daily duties will include:

  * Assist senior developers in developing solutions to the business’ requirements. 
  * Execute development tasks in line with the existing codebase. 
  * Assist in reproducing, isolating and fixing bugs. 
  * Refactoring code to better align with our latest architectures. 
  * Learning and implementing what you have learned during your workday. 

Core Technology Stack: c# (primarily net6+), MS SQL Server, WPF, asp.net APIs

You will be working with and reporting directly to the Software Development
Manager.

_ ** Full Time - On Site ** _

_ ** Brisbane North side ** _

** Why Work Here? **

  * You won’t be just a cog in the machine: 
    * Being part of a small team allows exposure and experience to all aspects of development from front end to backend web services. 
    * You get to see how people benefit from your development work. 
  * Development team is always evolving development practices and open to new ones. 
    * Use and learn DI, Layered development, MVVM, CQRS, SOLID principles. 
    * We often discuss new tech and new development ideas and have creative discussions on how we could use these ideas in our software. 
  * Adoption of new technology and tools 
    * For example, we've completed a migration from net 4.8 to .net 6 
    * Investigating and evaluating future front-end platforms to work with. 
  * It's not boring: 
    * There are always challenges that require creative solutions and thinking outside the box. 
    * As our market space is online selling, there are always innovative business ideas that require our skilled development team to implement to continue to put our business ahead of the pack. 

##  Attributes of the Successful Applicant

  * You're intelligent and like to converse with other intelligent people. 
  * You like to think and talk things through to end up at a more robust solution to development problems. 
  * You're not a know it all, but you have skills and like to learn as well as share your knowledge with others. 
  * Strong analytical and problem solving skills 
  * Excellent verbal and written communication skills 
  * Be able to demonstrate programming skills 
  * Be able to demonstrate communication of technical knowledge 

##  Required Proven Experience

  * Minimum of 1-2 years commercial application development experience with c# 
  * Ability to learn new technologies quickly; 
  * Have an existing, personal project that you have developed and are able to showcase to us. 
  * Some basic SQL knowledge 

##  Desirables

  * Entity Framework experience 
  * Web API (writing as well as communicating with) 

_ Please ensure you ** include a cover letter ** which includes a summary of
one of your most challenging development experiences so far. _

